WEBVTT

00:05.239 --> 00:07.808
OH. OH, NO. OH.
[growling, yelling on TV]

00:07.841 --> 00:10.211
HOW CAN YOU KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON IN THE MOVIE

00:10.244 --> 00:11.279
WITH YOUR EYES COVERED?

00:11.312 --> 00:12.280
IT'S TOO SCARY, DANNY.

00:12.313 --> 00:13.314
JUST DESCRIBE IT TO ME.

00:13.347 --> 00:15.216
OKAY, THE LIGHTS
ARE FLICKERING,

00:15.249 --> 00:17.218
FACELESS KIDS ARE COMING
THROUGH THE MIRROR RIGHT NOW.

00:17.251 --> 00:18.619
WHAT?
IT'S ALL GOING TO HELL.

00:18.652 --> 00:20.354
DANNY, STOP DESCRIBING
IT SO WELL,

00:20.388 --> 00:21.422
IT'S WORSE
THAN JUST WATCHING IT.

00:21.455 --> 00:23.057
WAIT A MINUTE...

00:23.091 --> 00:24.358
ISN'T THIS MOVIE STILL
IN THE THEATERS?

00:24.392 --> 00:26.427
MM-HMM. I STOLE IT
FROM THE INTERNET.

00:26.460 --> 00:27.695
YOU STOLE IT?

00:27.728 --> 00:28.796
YEAH, THAT'S HOW I GET
ALL MY MUSIC AND MOVIES.

00:28.829 --> 00:30.431
I GO TO THIS REALLY
COOL SITE.

00:30.464 --> 00:32.633
IT'S CALLED
VIDEODUMP.ALQAEDA.BIZ.

00:32.666 --> 00:33.734
YOU STEAL MUSIC TOO?

00:33.767 --> 00:34.735
OF COURSE, DANNY.

00:34.768 --> 00:35.703
DON'T YOU SUPPORT
THE ARTIST?

00:35.736 --> 00:37.771
WHAT ABOUT THE A&R GUY
WHO TOOK A CHANCE ON 'EM

00:37.805 --> 00:40.174
WITH THE LABEL BRASS?

00:40.208 --> 00:41.542
DON'T YOU THINK OF HIM?
NO.

00:41.575 --> 00:43.277
THAT'S AGAINST THE LAW.

00:43.311 --> 00:44.645
IT'S NOT AGAINST THE LAW
IF EVERYBODY DOES IT.

00:44.678 --> 00:46.314
IT'S LIKE HOW I PRETEND
TO BE IN THE ARMED FORCES

00:46.347 --> 00:47.215
SO I CAN BOARD
A PLANE EARLY.

00:47.248 --> 00:48.649
I NEVER BREAK THE LAW,
OKAY?

00:48.682 --> 00:50.118
WE GO DANCING,
I MAKE SURE

00:50.151 --> 00:52.220
THE CLUB HAS A VALID
CABARET LICENSE.

00:52.253 --> 00:53.221
[ding]

00:53.254 --> 00:54.488
OH, LOOK!

00:54.522 --> 00:56.457
THE FINAL HUNGER GAMES
DOWNLOADED.

00:56.490 --> 00:57.858
I'M GONNA BE SO SAD
WHEN THOSE ARE OVER

00:57.891 --> 00:59.493
AND I CAN'T STEAL THEM
ANYMORE.

00:59.527 --> 01:00.728
[alarm blaring]
(Danny)
WAIT A MINUTE.

01:00.761 --> 01:02.196
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?
[tapping keys]

01:02.230 --> 01:04.865
YOU--YOU CLICKED
A VIRUS.

01:04.898 --> 01:06.700
THIS IS A RUN-OF-THE-MILL
COMPUTER-DESTROYING VIRUS.

01:06.734 --> 01:08.769
ALL YOU NEED TO DO
IS GET A WHOLE NEW COMPUTER

01:08.802 --> 01:11.272
AND THEN TELL THE FBI
THAT YOURS WAS STOLEN.

01:11.305 --> 01:13.174
[ding ding]
OH, MY GOD,
THE CAMERA TURNED ON!

01:13.207 --> 01:14.442
- AAH!
- AAH!

01:14.475 --> 01:16.410
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE!

01:16.444 --> 01:17.511
[clatters]

01:17.545 --> 01:20.514
[upbeat music]

01:20.548 --> 01:28.556
*

01:32.393 --> 01:35.363
MA, TELL MINDY
ABOUT THAT WATER AEROBICS CLASS

01:35.396 --> 01:36.297
YOU SIGNED UP FOR.

01:36.330 --> 01:39.267
DANNY, YOU KEEP CALLING
IT "WATER AEROBICS."

01:39.300 --> 01:41.502
THAT'S JUST SO UNCOOL.

01:41.535 --> 01:45.473
IT'S CALLED "SYNCHRONIZED
SENIORS AQUA DISCO."

01:45.506 --> 01:47.208
I'M NOT SIGNING UP
FOR THAT.

01:47.241 --> 01:49.310
I DON'T WANNA GET
TOO MUSCULAR.

01:49.343 --> 01:50.811
I HAVE A DANCER'S BODY.

01:50.844 --> 01:53.181
ANNETTE, DO YOU HAVE
A BATHING SUIT?

01:53.214 --> 01:55.316
I COULD LEND YOU A BIKINI,
BUT I ONLY HAVE BOTTOMS

01:55.349 --> 01:56.617
'CAUSE I LIKE TO GO
AU NATUREL--

01:56.650 --> 01:58.419
OKAY, WE GOT IT.
WE GOT IT.

01:58.452 --> 02:00.221
NO, I'M GONNA WEAR
RICHIE'S SOCCER SHORTS

02:00.254 --> 02:02.156
AND MY GARFIELD T-SHIRT.

02:02.190 --> 02:04.258
DANNY'S WORRIED
I'LL GET OGLED AT.

02:04.292 --> 02:06.194
THE INSTRUCTOR'S CUBAN.
IT'S CULTURAL.

02:06.227 --> 02:07.728
A BAGGY T-SHIRT
AND SHORTS?

02:07.761 --> 02:08.862
IF YOU WEAR
THAT TO THE POOL,

02:08.896 --> 02:10.331
YOU'RE GONNA GET
STRAIGHT UP BULLIED.

02:10.364 --> 02:11.499
OH, COME ON.
WHO'S GONNA BULLY HER?

02:11.532 --> 02:12.866
LOOK AT THIS SWEET FACE.

02:12.900 --> 02:13.734
I WOULD.

02:13.767 --> 02:15.303
OKAY, I'M TAKING
YOU SHOPPING ON MONDAY.

02:15.336 --> 02:16.804
WE'RE GETTING YOU
A NEW SWIMSUIT.

02:16.837 --> 02:19.840
WOW, MY TWO FAVORITE GIRLS
GOING SHOPPING TOGETHER?

02:19.873 --> 02:21.409
I LOVE IT.

02:21.442 --> 02:23.877
WE'RE FINALLY GONNA GET SOME
ONE-ON-ONE TIME, MINDY.

02:23.911 --> 02:25.179
JUST YOU AND ME.

02:25.213 --> 02:26.914
I'M GONNA TELL YOU
ALL THE THINGS

02:26.947 --> 02:30.651
I WALKED IN ON DANNY DOING
OVER THE YEARS.

02:30.684 --> 02:31.819
MASTURBATING?

02:31.852 --> 02:33.254
OKAY.

02:33.287 --> 02:34.555
OH, GOD, DOT.
WHAT?

02:34.588 --> 02:37.225
COME ON, DOT.
THAT'S GROSS, ALL RIGHT?

02:37.258 --> 02:38.892
(Peter)
WELL, WE HAD A NIGHT
OF CRAZY SEX,

02:38.926 --> 02:40.328
AND NOW IT'S TIME
FOR THE PUNISHMENT.

02:40.361 --> 02:42.263
SO WHERE ARE WE GOING
TO BRUNCH?

02:42.296 --> 02:44.198
ACTUALLY, I HATE BRUNCH.

02:44.232 --> 02:46.300
BUT IF YOU'RE LIKE,
THE FIRST BRUNCH GUY

02:46.334 --> 02:47.335
IN THE HISTORY
OF THE WORLD,

02:47.368 --> 02:48.436
WE CAN GO GET SOME.

02:48.469 --> 02:49.470
SHUT UP.

02:49.503 --> 02:50.304
I JUST THOUGHT,
YOU KNOW,

02:50.338 --> 02:51.071
WE SHOULD DO
WHAT YOU WANNA DO TODAY

02:51.104 --> 02:53.541
SO YOU WANNA GO
TO SPIN CLASS,

02:53.574 --> 02:55.809
OR YOU WANT ME TO MEET
YOUR FRIEND'S NEW BABY?

02:55.843 --> 02:58.779
[laughs]
WHO IS THIS MONSTER
YOU'RE DESCRIBING?

02:58.812 --> 03:00.314
I'M NOT ONE
OF THOSE SAMPLE SALE,

03:00.348 --> 03:02.316
MANI-PEDI PRINCESSES.

03:02.350 --> 03:03.651
I JUST WANNA CHILL OUT
AND HAVE FUN.

03:03.684 --> 03:05.719
YOU LIKE,
MASTERED LIFE.

03:05.753 --> 03:06.787
I KNOW.

03:06.820 --> 03:07.788
I'M LIKE
THE MATTHEW MCCONAUGHEY

03:07.821 --> 03:09.390
OF THE ROMANCE NOVEL WORLD.

03:09.423 --> 03:11.425
SO ON YOUR IDEAL SUNDAY,
WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

03:11.459 --> 03:13.494
I WOULD DRINK A BUNCH
OF HARD LEMMYS

03:13.527 --> 03:16.264
AND MAKE OUTLANDISH
FOOTBALL BETS.

03:18.332 --> 03:19.500
WAIT.
WAIT, I'M SORRY.

03:19.533 --> 03:22.370
DID I SAY THE WRONG THING?
WE CAN DO WHATEVER YOU WANNA DO.

03:22.403 --> 03:23.404
YOU WANT ME TO PUT TOGETHER
SOME SHELVES?

03:23.437 --> 03:24.572
DO YOU WANNA GO VISIT
YOUR SISTER?

03:24.605 --> 03:25.539
NO, CALM DOWN.

03:25.573 --> 03:27.808
I'M JUST GONNA MAKE A RUN
TO THE LIQUOR STORE.

03:27.841 --> 03:29.277
YOUR MISSION,
WHILE I'M GONE,

03:29.310 --> 03:31.279
IS TO MELT CHEESE
ON SOMETHING.

03:31.312 --> 03:32.913
I BELIEVE IN YOU,
PETER.

03:32.946 --> 03:34.482
OKAY.

03:35.749 --> 03:37.585
GUYS, I HAVE AN ANNOUNCEMENT.

03:37.618 --> 03:39.553
WHAT? THAT YOU'RE RICH?
WE KNOW.

03:39.587 --> 03:41.389
TAMRA, CAN WE PLEASE
GO BACK TO THE DAYS

03:41.422 --> 03:43.724
BEFORE YOU FOUND
MY PAYSTUB IN THE TRASH?

03:43.757 --> 03:45.793
I'M TRYING TO TELL EVERYBODY
HERE THAT YOUR FRIEND ABBY

03:45.826 --> 03:46.794
IS MY PERFECT WOMAN.

03:46.827 --> 03:48.729
OH, SORRY.
GO ON, DR. P.

03:48.762 --> 03:51.365
DATING ABBY IS LIKE DATING
A RIDE THAT WON'T STOP.

03:51.399 --> 03:52.933
SHE'S AMAZING.

03:52.966 --> 03:54.034
ALL SHE DOES IS WRITE
TWO HOURS' WORTH

03:54.067 --> 03:55.703
OF SEXY STORIES
DURING THE DAY,

03:55.736 --> 03:57.037
AND THEN SHE'S
JUST HANGING.

03:57.070 --> 03:58.806
DAY DRINKING,
NIGHT SMOKING,

03:58.839 --> 04:00.874
AND SHE'S NOT ONE OF THESE
UPTIGHT MANHATTAN CHICKS

04:00.908 --> 04:02.376
THAT'S TRYING
TO GET ME TO CHANGE,

04:02.410 --> 04:04.278
OR MAKE ME WEAR PANTS
WHEN I LEAVE THE HOUSE,

04:04.312 --> 04:06.280
OR OBSESSED WITH THE NEW
BLOW DRY BAR DOWN THE BLOCK.

04:06.314 --> 04:08.382
BLOW DRY BAR?
HOW BASIC DO YOU THINK I AM?

04:08.416 --> 04:09.650
THIS IS FROM THE TOUSLE BAR.

04:09.683 --> 04:11.819
IT COST $100.
WHAT?

04:11.852 --> 04:13.321
YEAH, MORE THAN
THIS GUY'S RENT.

04:13.354 --> 04:14.322
YEAH!

04:14.355 --> 04:15.222
PETE, DON'T SCREW THIS UP.

04:15.255 --> 04:16.757
A LOW-MAINTENANCE GIRL
THAT LIKES TO HANG,

04:16.790 --> 04:18.492
NO DRAMA, NOT A LOT
OF PAMPERING.

04:18.526 --> 04:19.993
OH, LIKE YOU'RE NOT PAMPERED?

04:20.027 --> 04:21.695
WHY DON'T I GIVE MORGAN ONE
OF YOUR 9,000 MOISTURIZERS.

04:21.729 --> 04:22.996
WHY DON'T YOU GIVE THEM
TO MORGAN?

04:23.030 --> 04:24.865
I DON'T NEED ANY.
I'M ALWAYS WET.

04:24.898 --> 04:26.334
I'VE ACTUALLY FOUND IT
VERY GRATIFYING

04:26.367 --> 04:28.402
DATING A SERIOUS WOMAN
WHO CHALLENGES ME

04:28.436 --> 04:29.637
TO BE MY BEST SELF.

04:29.670 --> 04:33.341
OH, YOU KNOW, I TRIED DATING
A WOMAN LIKE THAT

04:33.374 --> 04:34.975
BUT SHE LEFT ME FOR YOU.

04:35.008 --> 04:36.810
SO I THINK I'LL STAY
ON THE TRACK THAT I'M ON, HUH?

04:36.844 --> 04:38.379
YUP. GOOD PLAN.
LOTS OF LUCK WITH IT.

04:38.412 --> 04:39.613
YEAH, YOU LIKE THAT PLAN?
WHOA!

04:39.647 --> 04:42.750
HUH? I GOT A MILLION BLACK BICS
IN THIS MUG.

04:42.783 --> 04:43.851
(Mindy)
OH, NO!

04:43.884 --> 04:45.553
(Annette)
MINDY, I'M COMING OUT.

04:45.586 --> 04:46.554
OKAY.

04:46.587 --> 04:47.555
TA-DA!

04:47.588 --> 04:48.556
AAH!

04:48.589 --> 04:49.690
IT'S GOOD, HUH?

04:49.723 --> 04:50.524
ANNETTE, THAT LOOKS LIKE
SOMETHING

04:50.558 --> 04:52.760
THAT RIHANNA WOULD WEAR
TO HEDONISM.

04:52.793 --> 04:53.994
OH, THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

04:54.027 --> 04:55.863
NO.
NO.

04:55.896 --> 04:58.065
I THINK THAT THOSE STRAPS
ARE JUST NOT AGE-APPROPRIATE.

04:58.098 --> 05:00.701
WHAT?
YOU SOUND JUST LIKE DANNY.

05:00.734 --> 05:03.871
WHATEVER HAPPENED
TO TAKING A RISK, HMM?

05:03.904 --> 05:06.340
SO WAS DANNY ALWAYS LIKE
CRAZY PSYCHO ABOUT RULES?

05:06.374 --> 05:09.543
UGH, DANNY WAS ALWAYS
SUCH AN ANGEL.

05:09.577 --> 05:11.812
I USED TO LISTEN IN
ON HIS CONFESSIONS--

05:11.845 --> 05:12.713
SO BORING.

05:12.746 --> 05:14.782
OF COURSE, THERE WERE
THE IMPURE THOUGHTS.

05:14.815 --> 05:18.386
ON AND ON ABOUT BIG,
MILKY-WHITE BREASTS--

05:18.419 --> 05:19.453
OKAY, HE HATES THOSE NOW.

05:19.487 --> 05:20.688
HE LIKES SMALL
ETHNIC BREASTS NOW.

05:20.721 --> 05:22.356
YEAH, WELL, I'M GLAD
HE'S WITH SOMEONE

05:22.390 --> 05:24.492
WHO PUSHES HIS BUTTONS
LIKE I DO.

05:24.525 --> 05:26.427
WHEN HE WAS LITTLE,
EVERY APRIL FOOLS' DAY,

05:26.460 --> 05:27.428
I USED TO PRETEND
I DIED.

05:27.461 --> 05:28.596
AAH!

05:28.629 --> 05:30.130
HOW DID YOU GET
NAKED SO FAST?

05:30.163 --> 05:31.565
AND THIS.

05:31.599 --> 05:33.534
AND THAT,
AND THAT.

05:33.567 --> 05:34.535
OKAY.

05:34.568 --> 05:37.137
AND ONE MORE THING.

05:37.170 --> 05:39.607
THIS IS FOR A SWIM CLASS.

05:39.640 --> 05:41.942
WELL, I GOTTA EAT,
DON'T I?

05:41.975 --> 05:43.611
WOULD YOU LIKE TO OPEN
A STORE CREDIT CARD?

05:43.644 --> 05:45.078
I SHOULDN'T.
MY CREDIT IS BAD.

05:45.112 --> 05:46.914
YOU GET A FUN EMAIL
ON YOUR BIRTHDAY.

05:46.947 --> 05:50.451
MY SOCIAL IS
637-70--

05:50.484 --> 05:52.386
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT'S JUST GONNA GET DECLINED.

05:52.420 --> 05:53.554
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
MY BOYFRIEND'S SOCIAL.

05:53.587 --> 05:56.123
IT'S 743-974--

06:07.801 --> 06:09.002
UH-OH, LOOK OUT!

06:09.036 --> 06:11.004
HERE COMES SHOPAHOLICS
ANONYMOUS.

06:11.038 --> 06:12.806
I BET YOU TWO DID SOME
DAMAGE, RIGHT?

06:12.840 --> 06:14.508
YEAH, THERE WAS SOME
DAMAGE DONE.

06:14.542 --> 06:15.976
CAN I SPEAK TO YOU PRIVATELY
IN MY OFFICE?

06:16.009 --> 06:17.010
SURE.

06:17.044 --> 06:20.748
DANNY, DON'T THINK I FORGOT
MY LITTLE BLUE ANGEL.

06:20.781 --> 06:21.882
OH, MA!
A BOMBER JACKET?

06:21.915 --> 06:22.883
YES!

06:22.916 --> 06:24.552
I ALWAYS WANTED ONE OF THOSE.

06:24.585 --> 06:26.820
I USED TO PLAY
TOP GUN WEARING A GARBAGE BAG,

06:26.854 --> 06:28.489
PRETENDING IT WAS
ONE OF THOSE.

06:28.522 --> 06:29.990
MA, THAT'S WAY TOO MUCH.

06:30.023 --> 06:31.492
IT WASN'T THAT MUCH.

06:31.525 --> 06:32.359
IT'S A LITTLE SNUG.

06:32.392 --> 06:33.561
MAYBE YOU COULD
EXCHANGE IT FOR ONE

06:33.594 --> 06:34.862
THAT'S A FEW SIZES
LARGER

06:34.895 --> 06:36.430
AND I COULD BORROW IT
A LITTLE BIT?

06:36.464 --> 06:37.898
NO, YOU SHOULD
TAKE IT OFF.

06:37.931 --> 06:38.899
OKAY.
OKAY.

06:38.932 --> 06:40.133
DANNY, YOU DESERVE IT.

06:40.167 --> 06:44.438
YOU WORK SO HARD AND YOU'VE GOT
SUCH A THOUGHTFUL GIRLFRIEND.

06:44.472 --> 06:45.873
WE REALLY CONNECTED.

06:45.906 --> 06:47.975
AH!
WHAT DO YOU THINK, MA?

06:48.008 --> 06:49.977
IT'S PERFECT!

06:50.010 --> 06:52.446
REQUESTING PERMISSION
TO FLY BY YOUR OFFICE, MINDY?

06:52.480 --> 06:53.547
WHAT?

06:53.581 --> 06:55.115
IT'S FROM THE MOVIE,
TOP GUN.

06:55.148 --> 06:56.717
OKAY,
I'VE NOT SEEN IT.

06:56.750 --> 06:59.152
I HAVE SEEN
THE PORN PARODY.

06:59.186 --> 07:01.555
OKAY, DO YOU WANNA TALK
TO ME IN PRIVATE, OR WHAT?

07:01.589 --> 07:02.590
OH, THAT'S WHAT YOU MEANT.

07:02.623 --> 07:05.626
UM, YEAH,
I WAS JUST GONNA SAY

07:05.659 --> 07:07.961
THAT YOUR MOM'S KEEPING HER BODY
REAL TIGHT.

07:07.995 --> 07:09.697
THAT'S SO NICE.

07:09.730 --> 07:11.231
REALLY? THAT'S KIND
OF A WEIRD THING TO SAY.

07:11.264 --> 07:13.801
WELL, SHE'S RIGHT.

07:13.834 --> 07:15.636
EXCUSE ME?

07:19.707 --> 07:21.174
OH, MY GOD!

07:21.208 --> 07:22.976
ARE YOU ABBY?
I AM.

07:23.010 --> 07:24.478
I HAVE AN IDEA
FOR A ROMANCE NOVEL

07:24.512 --> 07:25.979
THAT I WOULD LIKE
TO SELL YOU.

07:26.013 --> 07:27.648
OH, THAT SOUNDS GREAT.

07:27.681 --> 07:29.983
IT'S BASICALLY TWILIGHT,
BUT HERE'S THE TWIST.

07:30.017 --> 07:31.018
I'M THE GIRL.

07:31.051 --> 07:32.520
I THINK IT'S REALLY GOOD IDEA.

07:32.553 --> 07:33.521
YES.

07:33.554 --> 07:34.421
I THINK YOU SHOULD
WRITE IT THOUGH.

07:34.454 --> 07:35.923
OH, MY GOD.
THANK YOU FOR SAYING THAT.

07:35.956 --> 07:36.857
MY BOYFRIEND SAYS
I'M A QUOTE,

07:36.890 --> 07:38.859
"SHOCKINGLY BAD WRITER."

07:38.892 --> 07:40.127
OH.
YOU'RE COOL.

07:40.160 --> 07:41.695
YEAH, DOY.
SHE'S COOL.

07:41.729 --> 07:43.764
WE'VE ONLY BEEN
CHILLIN', GRILLIN'

07:43.797 --> 07:45.599
BLAZIN', LAZIN', ROLLIN'--

07:45.633 --> 07:47.935
OH, WHICH REMINDS ME, REMEMBER
THAT 24-HOUR DANCE PARTY

07:47.968 --> 07:50.538
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT,
THE ELECTRIC INSANITY BALL?

07:50.571 --> 07:52.005
I JUST READ AN ARTICLE THAT THEY
SHOULD SHUT THAT THING DOWN.

07:52.039 --> 07:52.740
IT SOUNDS GREAT.

07:52.773 --> 07:53.641
THE ELECTRIC INSANITY BALL?

07:53.674 --> 07:55.676
THAT'S ONLY THE COOLEST
PARTY IN TOWN.

07:55.709 --> 07:59.046
WELL, TAMRA GOT US ALL TICKETS,
SO...

07:59.079 --> 08:01.715
THAT IS SO AWESOME--
AW, SUCKS.

08:01.749 --> 08:02.850
I'M ON CALL.

08:02.883 --> 08:04.918
YOU CAN'T PARTY
WHEN YOU'RE ON CALL.

08:04.952 --> 08:06.554
HAD I KNOWN THAT, I NEVER
WOULD'VE BECOME A DOCTOR.

08:06.587 --> 08:08.121
YOU CANNOT BE ON CALL.
I'M GOING TO COVER FOR YOU.

08:08.155 --> 08:09.857
YOU HAVE TO GO
TO THIS PARTY.

08:09.890 --> 08:11.191
THAT'S WONDERFUL.
THANK YOU.
MM-HMM.

08:11.224 --> 08:12.993
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
PROBABLY KEEP COVERING FOR HIM

08:13.026 --> 08:14.862
FOR A WHILE, THOUGH,
BECAUSE AFTER TOMORROW NIGHT,

08:14.895 --> 08:16.296
HE'S GONNA BE FRIED
FOR LIKE A WEEK.

08:16.329 --> 08:17.565
OKAY...

08:17.598 --> 08:19.767
I ONCE HAD FRIES
FOR A WEEK.

08:19.800 --> 08:20.868
YEAH.

08:20.901 --> 08:23.871
['80s music]

08:23.904 --> 08:29.877
