08:29.910 --> 08:32.079
WELCOME TO THE DANGER ZONE.

08:32.112 --> 08:35.015
DID YOU TAKE THE HIGHWAY?

08:39.319 --> 08:41.021
I HAVE WONDERFUL NEWS,
MRS. RANDALL.

08:41.054 --> 08:41.989
[knock at door]

08:42.022 --> 08:43.557
JEREMY, I NEED YOUR OPINION
ON ETIQUETTE.

08:43.591 --> 08:44.892
YOU'RE TWO MONTHS PREGNANT.
GOOD-BYE.

08:44.925 --> 08:45.893
SIT DOWN.

08:45.926 --> 08:48.862
THANK YOU.

08:48.896 --> 08:50.931
YOU CHOSE WISELY,
COMING TO THE MOST

08:50.964 --> 08:52.299
WELL-MANNERED PERSON
IN THE OFFICE.

08:52.332 --> 08:54.635
OH, IT WAS BASED MORE
ON WHO WAS BACK FROM LUNCH.

08:54.668 --> 08:56.003
I'LL TAKE IT.
HOW CAN I HELP?

08:56.036 --> 08:58.271
DO YOU KNOW THAT BOMBER JACKET
THAT DANNY IS WEARING?

08:58.305 --> 09:00.574
I HATE IT, TOO.

09:00.608 --> 09:01.842
AREN'T WE DREADFUL?

09:01.875 --> 09:03.310
NO, NO, NO.
IT WAS SHOPLIFTED!

09:03.343 --> 09:05.312
BY DANNY'S MOM.
NO!

09:05.345 --> 09:07.047
I WANTED TO TELL HIM RIGHT AWAY,
BUT HE JUST LOVES IT SO MUCH.

09:07.080 --> 09:09.049
I SHOULD TELL HIM, RIGHT?
WRONG.

09:09.082 --> 09:11.184
THERE IS NO ADVANTAGE TO SHINING
LIGHT ON FAMILIAL SCANDAL.

09:11.218 --> 09:12.753
IN BRITAIN,
WE HAVE AN EXPRESSION:

09:12.786 --> 09:15.656
"KEEP CALM AND DON'T MENTION
UNCLE SUSAN IN THE ATTIC."

09:15.689 --> 09:16.657
OH, MY GOD.

09:16.690 --> 09:18.726
THAT MIGHT JUST BE
MY FAMILY.

09:18.759 --> 09:19.727
IT'S GONE!

09:19.760 --> 09:20.728
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE IT IS.

09:20.761 --> 09:22.195
IT'S A SYMBOL
OF MY LOVE FOR YOU.

09:22.229 --> 09:23.263
I KNOW.
BUT YOU--

09:23.296 --> 09:25.899
OH, MY GOD. DID YOU BUY
TAMRA AN ENGAGEMENT RING?

09:25.933 --> 09:28.769
OH, NO, I'M OUT OF TOWN
FOR THE WEDDING, WHENEVER IT IS.

09:28.802 --> 09:29.970
NO, NO.
IT WAS A CHARM BRACELET

09:30.003 --> 09:31.171
FROM THE DRUG STORE.

09:31.204 --> 09:33.741
BUT IT'S THREE MONTHS' SALARY
DOWN THE DRAIN.

09:33.774 --> 09:35.909
MY GOD,
WE PAY YOU SO LITTLE.

09:35.943 --> 09:38.946
HELLO! I'M ON A POSTER
FOR A POVERTY CAMPAIGN.

09:38.979 --> 09:40.714
DON'T FREAK OUT, TAMRA.
I LOSE MY STUFF ALL THE TIME.

09:40.748 --> 09:42.215
YOU JUST HAVE TO RETRACE
YOUR STEPS.

09:42.249 --> 09:44.918
WHENEVER I CAN'T FIND MY PHONE,
IT'S USUALLY IN THE FREEZER,

09:44.952 --> 09:46.286
NEXT TO MY ICE CREAM BARS.

09:46.319 --> 09:48.288
OKAY, THE LAST TIME
I REMEMBER HAVING IT

09:48.321 --> 09:50.991
IS WHEN I TOOK IT OFF
TO SHOW DR. C'S MOM.

09:51.024 --> 09:53.060
HOLD UP.
YOU SHOWED IT TO ANNETTE?

09:53.093 --> 09:56.363
YEAH, SHE WAS LIKE, "THAT'S
FIERCE AS HELL. NO SHADE."

09:56.396 --> 09:58.198
I COULD BE PARAPHRASING.

09:58.231 --> 09:59.399
[doorbell dings]

09:59.432 --> 10:02.002
MINDY!
WHAT A SURPRISE!

10:02.035 --> 10:03.804
COME ON IN.
DOT AND I ARE WATCHING

10:03.837 --> 10:04.805
PASSION OF THE CHRIST.

10:04.838 --> 10:07.708
WHAT THEY DID TO THAT MAN--

10:07.741 --> 10:09.877
POOR MEL.

10:09.910 --> 10:11.244
I ACTUALLY CAN'T STAY.

10:11.278 --> 10:13.280
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT SOMETHING.

10:13.313 --> 10:15.916
ONE OF OUR NURSES
LOST HER NEW BRACELET.

10:15.949 --> 10:16.917
WHICH NURSE?

10:16.950 --> 10:20.253
SHE'S TALL, VERY PRETTY,
MID-20s, SHE'S BLACK.

10:20.287 --> 10:22.055
YOU COULD'VE JUST SAID TAMRA.

10:22.089 --> 10:25.025
IS IT POSSIBLE THAT YOU,
I DON'T KNOW, LIKE,

10:25.058 --> 10:28.128
TRIED IT ON AND THEN
FORGOT TO GIVE IT BACK TO HER?

10:28.161 --> 10:30.964
ARE YOU ACCUSING ME
OF STEALING?

10:30.998 --> 10:32.132
WHAT?

10:32.165 --> 10:34.201
STEALING?
NO!

10:34.234 --> 10:35.869
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!

10:35.903 --> 10:37.237
HOW DARE YOU.

10:37.270 --> 10:38.739
(Dot)
CAN YOU TWO KEEP IT DOWN?

10:38.772 --> 10:40.307
THIS IS MY FAVORITE PART.

10:40.340 --> 10:42.375
JUDAS IS GETTING HIS COINS.

10:42.409 --> 10:43.811
MY HOUSE, DOT!

10:43.844 --> 10:44.912
YEAH, DOT.
JUST SHUT UP!

10:44.945 --> 10:46.179
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOMETHING.

10:46.213 --> 10:47.915
PLEASE, I WILL NOT TELL
A SOUL--

10:47.948 --> 10:50.217
[phone chimes]

10:50.250 --> 10:51.218
WHAT?

10:51.251 --> 10:52.285
OH NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

10:52.319 --> 10:53.987
(Dot)
GREAT, I MISSED THE COINS.

10:54.021 --> 10:55.088
TAMRA, YOU FOUND
YOUR BRACELET?

10:55.122 --> 10:56.023
WHERE WAS IT?

10:56.056 --> 10:57.958
I FORGOT I TRIED IT
ON MY ANKLE FOR A WHILE.

10:57.991 --> 10:58.992
ALWAYS THE LAST PLACE
YOU LOOK.

10:59.026 --> 11:00.961
IT WAS THE FIRST PLACE
I LOOKED.

11:00.994 --> 11:02.229
OH, HEY, BABY.

11:02.262 --> 11:03.797
HEY.

11:03.831 --> 11:04.998
UM, I HAVE AN IDEA
FOR TONIGHT.

11:05.032 --> 11:06.734
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK
WE SHOULD DO?

11:06.767 --> 11:08.035
JUST COMPLETELY UNPLUG.
LIKE DON'T USE TECHNOLOGY.

11:08.068 --> 11:09.937
DON'T USE OUR CELL PHONES.
JUST YOU AND ME.

11:09.970 --> 11:11.238
OH, I LIKE THAT.

11:11.271 --> 11:12.105
IT'D BE GOOD FOR ME
TO GET AWAY

11:12.139 --> 11:13.907
FROM MY HEALTHY RECIPE SITES
FOR A NIGHT.

11:13.941 --> 11:15.175
[phone vibrates]
THAT'S GREAT.

11:15.208 --> 11:16.309
ONE SECOND.

11:16.343 --> 11:17.911
WOW, EIGHT MISSED CALLS
FROM MA.

11:17.945 --> 11:19.780
SHE PROBABLY JUST BUTT-DIALED
YOU, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

11:19.813 --> 11:20.781
HELLO?

11:20.814 --> 11:21.782
OH, GOD.

11:21.815 --> 11:23.183
HUH?

11:23.216 --> 11:25.753
MINDY DID WHAT?

11:28.355 --> 11:29.790
MA, PLEASE, CALM DOWN.

11:29.823 --> 11:31.759
MINDY DOESN'T UNDERSTAND
SOCIAL MORES.

11:31.792 --> 11:33.894
SHE'S FROM BOSTON.
MA--

11:33.927 --> 11:35.362
MA?
[dial tone]

11:35.395 --> 11:36.797
GREAT, SHE HUNG UP.

11:36.830 --> 11:38.766
THIS IS THE WORST THING
YOU'VE EVER DONE.

11:38.799 --> 11:40.033
AND I'M INCLUDING WHEN YOU
THOUGHT THAT CAB DRIVER

11:40.067 --> 11:41.735
WAS THE GUY
FROM CAPTAIN PHILLIPS.

11:41.769 --> 11:43.837
YOU DIDN'T SEE HIM.
HE WAS VERY GAUNT.

11:43.871 --> 11:46.373
HE LOOKED NOTHING LIKE
THE GUY FROM CAPTAIN PHILLIPS.

11:46.406 --> 11:48.208
I THINK IT WAS JUST A LITTLE BIT
TOO MUCH, TOO SOON,

11:48.241 --> 11:49.476
FOR ME AND YOUR MOM.

11:49.509 --> 11:51.344
BUT SHE'S GOING TO GET
OVER THIS, EVENTUALLY.

11:51.378 --> 11:53.013
AND UNTIL THEN,
WHENEVER SHE COMES OVER,

11:53.046 --> 11:54.314
I'M JUST GONNA SIT
IN THE CLOSET,

11:54.347 --> 11:55.415
READ AN ARCHIE COMIC,
AND STAY THERE

11:55.448 --> 11:56.583
UNTIL SHE LEAVES.

11:56.616 --> 11:58.385
AND YOU CAN JUST SLIDE A PLATE
OF FOOD UNDER THE DOOR.

11:58.418 --> 11:59.787
NO, NO, THAT'S NOT
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN, OKAY?

11:59.820 --> 12:00.921
TONIGHT, YOU AND ME
ARE GOING OVER

12:00.954 --> 12:01.922
TO MA'S HOUSE
FOR DINNER.

12:01.955 --> 12:04.091
GREAT, SO SHE FORGAVE ME.
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

12:04.124 --> 12:04.958
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

12:04.992 --> 12:06.927
YOU'RE DEALING
WITH CATHOLICS NOW, OKAY?

12:06.960 --> 12:08.061
THIS IS A GUILT DINNER,
WHICH MEANS

12:08.095 --> 12:09.496
SHE'S GONNA TORTURE YOU.

12:09.529 --> 12:10.530
GET READY TO REPENT, LAHIRI.

12:10.563 --> 12:13.200
NOW GO HOME AND PUT ON SOMETHING
BLACK AND MODEST.

12:13.233 --> 12:16.303
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

12:16.336 --> 12:18.171
NOW, THE ONLY THING
I HAVE THAT'S BLACK

12:18.205 --> 12:19.940
IS MY CATWOMAN COSTUME.
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

12:19.973 --> 12:21.775
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I WILL JUST ZIP IT UP

12:21.809 --> 12:23.844
ALL THE WAY TO THE TOP.

12:23.877 --> 12:26.546
AND DEFINITELY UNDERWEAR.

12:26.579 --> 12:28.782
YEAH, OH--YEAH.

12:29.582 --> 12:31.151
OH, HEY, PETE.
HEY, BUDDY.

12:31.184 --> 12:32.419
I GOT BAD NEWS FOR YOU.

12:32.452 --> 12:33.453
MINDY CAN'T COVER
FOR YOU TONIGHT.

12:33.486 --> 12:35.222
SHE'S GOT A DINNER DATE
WITH MY MA.

12:35.255 --> 12:36.824
FIRST THING
ON THE MENU--CROW.

12:36.857 --> 12:37.858
FOR DESSERT:
HUMBLE PIE.

12:37.891 --> 12:38.792
APPETIZERS--

12:38.826 --> 12:41.061
NO, NO, NO, MINDY'S GOTTA
COVER FOR ME.

12:41.094 --> 12:43.263
ABBY'S TAKING ME
TO AN ALL-NIGHT DANCE PARTY.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.298
AND IF I'M ON CALL,
I HAVE TO BE SOBER.

12:45.332 --> 12:46.934
AND I'M NOT TALKING
"TAKE THE S.A.T.s" SOBER.

12:46.967 --> 12:49.436
I'M TALKING LIKE,
SOBER SOBER.

12:49.469 --> 12:50.971
WHY DO YOU NEED
TO BE DRUNK TO DANCE?

12:51.004 --> 12:53.006
DOESN'T THAT MAKE
YOUR MOVES LESS PRECISE?

12:53.040 --> 12:55.242
ACTUALLY, NO. IT HAS
THE OPPOSITE EFFECT ON ME.

12:55.275 --> 12:57.377
AND I GUESS I COULD HANG OUT
WITH ABBY NOT MESSED UP

12:57.410 --> 13:00.280
BUT WE'VE NEVER DONE
THAT BEFORE.

13:00.313 --> 13:01.248
YEAH, BUT IF IT'S
THE REAL THING,

13:01.281 --> 13:02.983
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO DO IT EVENTUALLY, RIGHT?

13:03.016 --> 13:05.953
YEAH, I SEE YOUR POINT.

13:05.986 --> 13:08.055
WHY ARE YOU LOOKING
AT ME LIKE THAT?

13:08.088 --> 13:09.422
YOU LOOK A LOT LIKE MINDY
IN THAT OUTFIT.

13:09.456 --> 13:10.590
KEEP YOUR EYES UP HERE, MAN.

13:10.623 --> 13:11.591
YOU LOOK GOOD.

13:11.624 --> 13:13.360
SHUT UP!

13:13.393 --> 13:16.363
[dance music]

13:16.396 --> 13:22.302
*

13:22.335 --> 13:23.436
PETER, WHAT'S WRONG?

13:23.470 --> 13:25.238
IT DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
YOU'RE HAVING FUN.

13:25.272 --> 13:27.875
NO, I THINK THE GRANOLA BAR
I ATE HASN'T KICKED IN YET.

13:27.908 --> 13:29.076
OH.

13:29.109 --> 13:30.978
YEAH, YOU'RE DANCING
LIKE AN UNDERCOVER COP.

13:31.011 --> 13:33.513
MORGAN,
WHAT ARE YOU ON?

13:33.546 --> 13:34.381
NOTHING.

13:34.414 --> 13:36.383
HEY, YOU CAN'T HAVE
JUST LIKE, ONE BEER?

13:36.416 --> 13:39.052
I'M ON CALL.
I GOTTA SAY SOBER.

13:39.086 --> 13:41.321
YOU KNOW?
I HAVE TO BE ON MY A-GAME.
[phone vibrates]

13:41.354 --> 13:42.890
OH, YOU WANNA BE
ON SOME A-GAME?

13:42.923 --> 13:45.458
'CAUSE I THINK
THE BOUNCER'S SELLING SOME.

13:45.492 --> 13:46.860
NO, ACTUALLY,
I JUST GOT A TEXT.

13:46.894 --> 13:48.095
I HAVE TO GO
TO THE HOSPITAL

13:48.128 --> 13:49.129
FOR A DELIVERY.

13:49.162 --> 13:49.997
OH, YOU WANT ME
TO GO WITH YOU?

13:50.030 --> 13:52.099
NO, NO, YOU STAY,
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

13:52.132 --> 13:53.466
COME BACK LATER.

13:53.500 --> 13:54.601
AND BRING THE BABY.

13:54.634 --> 13:56.303
DR. P, COULD I HAVE
YOUR UNDERWEAR

13:56.336 --> 13:58.238
IF YOU'RE GONNA LEAVE?
MINE'S ALL SOAKING WET.

13:58.271 --> 13:59.372
NO, YEAH, I THINK
I'M JUST GONNA GO.

13:59.406 --> 14:00.440
WITH ALL MY CLOTHES.

14:00.473 --> 14:02.609
IT'S NOT URINE.
IT'S SWEAT.

14:02.642 --> 14:04.244
(Annette)
LET'S ALL BOW OUR HEADS.

14:04.277 --> 14:09.216
DEAR LORD, PLEASE HELP US
FIND IT IN OUR HEARTS

14:09.249 --> 14:12.419
TO FORGIVE THE MOST
TERRIBLE OF CRIMES,

14:12.452 --> 14:16.256
THE WRONGFUL ACCUSATIONS
LEVERAGED AGAINST

14:16.289 --> 14:18.258
THE INNOCENT ELDERLY.

14:18.291 --> 14:19.927
YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME
WITH THIS.

14:19.960 --> 14:23.196
OH LORD,
WHOSE WRATH KNOWS NO BOUNDS,

14:23.230 --> 14:25.632
PLEASE SPARE MINDY
THE PESTILENCE,

14:25.665 --> 14:28.435
BOILS, AND FAMINE
YOU ARE SURELY CONSIDERING

14:28.468 --> 14:29.536
RIGHT NOW.

14:29.569 --> 14:31.939
ALTHOUGH, A LITTLE FAMINE
WOULDN'T BE THE WORST THING

14:31.972 --> 14:32.940
IN THE WORLD.

14:32.973 --> 14:37.244
[ah-hem, ah-hem,
ah-ah-ah-hem]

14:37.277 --> 14:40.213
AND PLEASE WATCH OVER
DOT, RICHIE, DANNY,

14:40.247 --> 14:41.481
AND THE STRAY CATS.

14:41.514 --> 14:42.615
AMEN.

14:42.649 --> 14:44.351
(all)
AMEN.
GREAT ONE, MOM.

14:44.384 --> 14:48.521
THAT WAS A BEAUTIFUL
AND KIND OF POINTED PRAYER.

14:48.555 --> 14:50.657
ANNETTE, I JUST WANTED
TO SAY TO YOU, AGAIN,

14:50.690 --> 14:53.093
HOW SORRY I AM
FOR EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED.

14:53.126 --> 14:55.028
IT'S FINE.
WATER UNDER THE BRIDGE.

14:55.062 --> 14:56.496
REALLY?

14:56.529 --> 14:57.330
LET'S JUST MOVE FORWARD

14:57.364 --> 14:59.599
AND ENJOY THIS ROAST CHICKEN
TOGETHER.

14:59.632 --> 15:03.203
OH, AND JUST SO THAT MINDY KNOWS
THAT I PAID FOR THE CHICKEN,

15:03.236 --> 15:05.905
I HAD THE RECEIPT FRAMED
FOR HER. DOT.

15:07.040 --> 15:09.276
OKAY, THAT IS ENOUGH.
PUT THAT AWAY, DOT.

15:09.309 --> 15:10.710
HEY, MOM.

15:10.743 --> 15:13.713
THE REASON THAT I THOUGHT YOU
STOLE THE BRACELET, ANNETTE,

15:13.746 --> 15:18.351
IS BECAUSE I SAW YOU STEAL
THE JACKET THAT DANNY'S WEARING.

15:18.385 --> 15:20.187
MINDY, PLEASE STOP.

15:20.220 --> 15:22.990
I WILL NOT STOP, DANNY.
I SAW IT WITH MY TWO EYES.

15:23.023 --> 15:24.624
AND I HAVE PERFECT VISION
BECAUSE I'M STILL YOUNG.

15:24.657 --> 15:25.925
ASK HER.

15:27.560 --> 15:28.628
WHAT WAS THE QUESTION AGAIN?

15:28.661 --> 15:31.364
ASK HER IF SHE STOLE IT.

15:31.398 --> 15:34.968
MA, DID YOU STEAL THE JACKET?

15:35.002 --> 15:39.072
YES! YES! YES! I WALKED OUT
OF THE STORE WITH THE JACKET.

15:39.106 --> 15:40.173
WHAT?

15:40.207 --> 15:41.241
THANK YOU!
THANK YOU.

15:41.274 --> 15:44.211
IT'S JUST THAT MY MIND,
SOMETIMES IT JUST GETS FOGGY

15:44.244 --> 15:46.046
WHEN I DON'T TAKE MY FISH OIL.

15:46.079 --> 15:49.382
BUT AS SOON AS I REALIZED IT,
I WENT RIGHT BACK IN THERE,

15:49.416 --> 15:51.151
AND I PAID FOR IT!

15:51.184 --> 15:52.619
WELL, THERE YOU GO.
WHAT? WHEN?

15:52.652 --> 15:54.154
WHEN YOU WERE BUSY
PUMPING QUARTERS

15:54.187 --> 15:56.156
INTO THE MASSAGE CHAIR
AND GROANING.

15:56.189 --> 15:58.291
I DIDN'T WANNA TELL YOU,
DANNY,

15:58.325 --> 16:00.193
BECAUSE I'M ALREADY
SUCH A BURDEN.

16:00.227 --> 16:02.162
MA, YOU'RE NOT A BURDEN,
OKAY?

16:02.195 --> 16:03.163
NO, NO, NO, NO.

16:03.196 --> 16:04.531
YOU'RE MY BEATING HEART, MA.

16:04.564 --> 16:08.168
I DON'T SEE HOW YOU
COME BACK FROM THIS.

16:08.201 --> 16:10.303
SAYONARA.

16:10.337 --> 16:11.771
YEAH.
OH--OOH.

16:11.804 --> 16:13.173
YEAH, YOUR WATCH IS CAUGHT--

16:13.206 --> 16:14.341
YEAH, IT'S MY WATCH.
OUCH.

16:14.374 --> 16:16.109
IT'S REALLY STUCK.

16:16.143 --> 16:19.046
[all gasping]

16:21.214 --> 16:24.051
MAYBE THEY FORGOT
TO TAKE OFF THE TAG?

16:26.353 --> 16:27.620
YOU'RE A SHOPLIFTER?

16:27.654 --> 16:30.357
MOM, I'M QUESTIONING
MY ENTIRE CHILDHOOD RIGHT NOW.

16:30.390 --> 16:32.325
CHRISTMAS PRESENTS,
MY BASEBALL GEAR--

16:32.359 --> 16:33.660
DID YOU STEAL THOSE TOO?

16:33.693 --> 16:35.595
NO, NO, OF COURSE NOT!

16:35.628 --> 16:39.299
I JUST STARTED DOING IT
LAST YEAR, HERE AND THERE.

16:39.332 --> 16:41.301
I--MAYBE I'VE JUST BEEN
BORED LATELY.

16:41.334 --> 16:43.170
COULD IT BE THE DANGER?

16:43.203 --> 16:45.138
MAYBE IT'S A SEXUAL THING.

16:45.172 --> 16:47.107
NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, ITS--

16:47.140 --> 16:48.408
HOW COULD IT BE THAT?
IT'S NOT--

16:48.441 --> 16:50.110
NO, DON'T SAY THAT.
IT'S NOT A SEXUAL THING.

16:50.143 --> 16:51.411
THAT'S DISGUSTING.

16:51.444 --> 16:54.414
MA, LOOK, TOMORROW,
YOU'RE GOING TO THE STORE,

16:54.447 --> 16:55.648
AND YOU'RE GONNA RETURN
THE JACKET,

16:55.682 --> 16:57.184
AND YOU'RE GONNA APOLOGIZE.

16:57.217 --> 16:58.818
I'D RATHER NOT,
IF IT'S ALL THE SAME TO YOU.

16:58.851 --> 17:00.220
IT'S NOT ALL THE SAME
TO ME, MA.

17:00.253 --> 17:01.754
I'M SORRY, YOU'RE GOING.

17:01.788 --> 17:03.523
WE'RE ALL GOING.
EXCEPT DOT.

17:03.556 --> 17:06.626
OH, LIKE THIS TRIP WOULD APPEAL
TO ME IN ANY WAY.

17:06.659 --> 17:08.461
ANNETTE, I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
THAT THE EMBARRASSMENT

17:08.495 --> 17:10.830
YOU FEEL RIGHT NOW
IS EQUAL TO THE TRIUMPH

17:10.863 --> 17:12.365
THAT I FEEL,
AND IF THAT'S THE CASE--

17:12.399 --> 17:13.700
OKAY, BABY, I'M REALLY SORRY
THAT I DOUBTED YOU

17:13.733 --> 17:15.302
BUT IF YOU DON'T SHUT UP
RIGHT NOW,

17:15.335 --> 17:16.536
MY MOM'S GONNA HIT YOU OVER
THE HEAD WITH A ROLLING PIN.

17:16.569 --> 17:17.537
OKAY,
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT THEN?

17:17.570 --> 17:19.106
I'LL JUST GO GET MY PURSE.

17:19.139 --> 17:21.274
JUST MAKE SURE THAT ALL
THE MONEY IS STILL IN THERE.

17:21.308 --> 17:22.575
OKAY, THAT'S IT--
OKAY, MA! MA! MA!

17:22.609 --> 17:23.743
MA, MA, CALM DOWN.

17:23.776 --> 17:25.445
(Peter)
HERE HE IS.
MAN OF THE HOUR.

17:34.354 --> 17:35.522
[phone vibrates]

17:51.504 --> 17:53.173
WE'D LIKE TO RETURN
THIS JACKET.

17:53.206 --> 17:55.708
SURE.
CAN I SEE YOUR RECEIPT?

17:55.742 --> 17:57.477
UH, I WISH I HAD ONE.

17:57.510 --> 18:01.348
BUT UNFORTUNATELY,
THERE WAS NEVER A RECEIPT

18:01.381 --> 18:02.815
FOR THIS ITEM.

18:02.849 --> 18:05.585
SHE'S A GOOD WOMAN,
MY MOM, SINGLE MOM.

18:05.618 --> 18:07.220
LET ME TELL YOU
WHEN MY DAD LEFT--

18:07.254 --> 18:08.755
THE JACKET HAS INK
ALL OVER IT.

18:08.788 --> 18:10.390
THIS WAS CLEARLY STOLEN.

18:10.423 --> 18:12.359
YES, AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
SHE IS VERY SORRY.

18:12.392 --> 18:13.693
WE ARE GOING TO GROUND HER
FOR A WEEK.

18:13.726 --> 18:15.262
YES, WE ARE.

18:15.295 --> 18:17.464
MISS, YOU KNOW, WHEN YOU'RE OVER
60 IN THIS COUNTRY,

18:17.497 --> 18:18.531
YOU ARE INVISIBLE.

18:18.565 --> 18:20.333
I TOOK THAT JACKET
TO MAKE A POLITICAL STATEMENT--

18:20.367 --> 18:21.801
SHH, NO, NO.
SHUT UP, SHUT UP.

18:21.834 --> 18:23.670
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE GONNA PAY FOR
THE JACKET AND BE ON OUR WAY.

18:23.703 --> 18:25.338
IF YOU WANT,
YOU CAN TAKE A PICTURE OF HER.

18:25.372 --> 18:27.474
THAT WOULD REALLY SCARE HER.
GREAT IDEA.

18:27.507 --> 18:30.377
I'M SORRY, BUT THIS JACKET
COST OVER $500.

18:30.410 --> 18:32.245
IT COULD BE A FELONY CHARGE.

18:32.279 --> 18:35.548
I'M AFRAID I'M GOING TO HAVE
TO CALL...GARY.

18:35.582 --> 18:37.550
GARY?

18:37.584 --> 18:40.287
DID YOU HEAR HER?
I'M GOING TO JAIL!

18:40.320 --> 18:41.388
YEAH, AND I'M GONNA HAVE
TO BREAK YOU OUT.

18:41.421 --> 18:42.589
I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO DIG TUNNELS.

18:42.622 --> 18:43.690
MINDY CAN DIG!

18:43.723 --> 18:44.891
OKAY, LISTEN UP, LISTEN UP,
WE ARE NOT DOING THIS.

18:44.924 --> 18:46.559
WE ARE MAKING A RUN FOR IT.

18:46.593 --> 18:48.395
WHAT, ARE YOU CRAZY?
WE'RE NOT GONNA RUN FOR IT.

18:48.428 --> 18:49.762
WE'RE GONNA SIT HERE
AND FACE THE MUSIC.

18:49.796 --> 18:51.198
[slap]
SNAP OUT OF IT.

18:51.231 --> 18:52.332
DANNY, WE'RE NOT LETTING
YOUR MOM GET ARRESTED

18:52.365 --> 18:53.466
BECAUSE IT'S THE LETTER
OF THE LAW.

18:53.500 --> 18:54.434
THIS IS FAMILY.

18:54.467 --> 18:56.169
WHEN OUR SON GETS ARRESTED
IN THE HAMPTONS

18:56.203 --> 18:57.370
FOR HAVING A BAR FIGHT,
I'M GONNA DRIVE HIS ASS

18:57.404 --> 18:58.938
TO MEXICO IN THE BACK
OF A CHICKEN TRUCK.

18:58.971 --> 19:00.440
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

19:03.343 --> 19:04.177
RUN.

19:06.446 --> 19:10.483
I'M SORRY, TELL GARY
I'LL SEND HIM A CHECK.

19:10.517 --> 19:12.385
(Abby)
HEY, PETER, WHAT'S SHAKING?

19:12.419 --> 19:14.454
(Peter)
SOME HARDCORE EPIPHANIES,
ACTUALLY.

19:14.487 --> 19:15.622
HEY, WHAT HAPPENED TO
YOU LAST NIGHT?

19:15.655 --> 19:16.889
YOU KNOW, I JUST--
I WENT HOME,

19:16.923 --> 19:20.360
I TOOK A SHOWER, DID THE DISHES,
KIND OF JUST WENT TO BED EARLY.

19:20.393 --> 19:22.862
BUMMER.
ACTUALLY,
IT WAS PRETTY GREAT.

19:22.895 --> 19:25.798
LOOK, ABBY, I THINK
WE NEED TO TALK.

19:25.832 --> 19:27.434
OH, NO.

19:27.467 --> 19:29.636
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO CROSS AROUND AND--

19:29.669 --> 19:30.770
YOU'RE GONNA SIT,
AREN'T YOU?

19:30.803 --> 19:33.206
DON'T DO THE--
YEAH.

19:33.240 --> 19:34.774
PETER, I'VE WRITTEN ENOUGH
OVERWROUGHT BREAKUP SCENES,

19:34.807 --> 19:36.509
SO I KNOW HOW THIS GOES.

19:36.543 --> 19:37.844
ABBY, I THINK--
(both)
YOU'RE GREAT.

19:37.877 --> 19:39.279
WHOA!

19:39.312 --> 19:41.481
I JUST, I'M LEARNING
THAT I, UH,

19:41.514 --> 19:43.283
I THINK I NEED SOMEONE
WHO WANTS ME TO PUT PANTS ON

19:43.316 --> 19:44.417
BEFORE I LEAVE THE HOUSE

19:44.451 --> 19:47.220
AND MAYBE SOMEONE
WHO LIKES BRUNCH.

19:47.254 --> 19:49.822
WELL,
I CAN'T HELP YOU THERE.

19:49.856 --> 19:51.391
IT WAS FUN THOUGH, RIGHT?

19:51.424 --> 19:53.993
OH, YEAH.
A LOT OF FUN,

19:54.026 --> 19:55.595
WELL, IF YOU EVER WANT
TO GET BAKED

19:55.628 --> 19:59.232
AND GO TO A RENAISSANCE FAIR,
THEN I'M YOUR M'LADY.

19:59.266 --> 20:01.501
WELL, THAT SOUNDS M'NICE.

20:01.534 --> 20:05.638
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL SEE YOU.

20:05.672 --> 20:06.639
BYE, ABBY.

20:06.673 --> 20:08.275
BYE.

20:12.845 --> 20:15.582
HEY, PETER, WHAT'S SHAKIN'?

20:15.615 --> 20:16.649
HMM?

20:16.683 --> 20:19.018
WAS I JUST IN HERE?

20:19.051 --> 20:21.954
I'M SORRY,
I'M SO HIGH.

20:21.988 --> 20:25.358
THAT'S HILARIOUS.

20:25.392 --> 20:27.760
YOU REMEMBER WE BROKE UP,
RIGHT?

20:29.896 --> 20:32.999
DANNY, GUESS WHO PAID
FOR HER FIRST SONG, EVER!

20:33.032 --> 20:35.368
IS THAT WHY YOU WERE LOCKED
IN THE BATHROOM FOR AN HOUR?

20:35.402 --> 20:36.603
MM-HMM.
THAT AND OTHER REASONS.

20:36.636 --> 20:39.506
HEY, YOU KNOW?
THANKS FOR HELPING MA OUT.

20:39.539 --> 20:41.541
I GOTTA ADMIT, RUNNING OUT
OF THE STORE LIKE THAT,

20:41.574 --> 20:44.877
I...I KIND OF GOT A TINGLE.

20:44.911 --> 20:46.913
OH, MY GOD, DANNY,
ARE YOU BREAKING BAD?

20:46.946 --> 20:48.515
RELAX, I'M STILL
ALL ABOUT THE RULES,

20:48.548 --> 20:50.417
I'M JUST SAYING, YOU KNOW,
THE NUMBER ONE RULE

20:50.450 --> 20:52.385
SHOULD BE "FAMILY FIRST."

20:52.419 --> 20:53.586
I LIKE THAT.
YEAH?

20:53.620 --> 20:55.622
I THINK THAT YOU
ARE BECOMING A BAD BOY.

20:55.655 --> 20:56.623
AND I LIKE IT.

20:56.656 --> 20:57.790
YOU LIKE IT?
MM-HMM.

20:57.824 --> 20:59.058
YEAH?

20:59.091 --> 21:01.661
DO YOU LIKE WHEN I WEAR
STOLEN MERCHANDISE?

21:01.694 --> 21:03.430
OOH.
DO YOU LIKE THAT?

21:03.463 --> 21:04.464
MM-HMM.

21:06.599 --> 21:07.600
HOW ABOUT THIS?

21:07.634 --> 21:08.635
WHOA.

21:11.103 --> 21:13.340
I GOT A REAL NEED.

21:13.373 --> 21:14.941
THE NEED TO SQUEEZE.

21:14.974 --> 21:16.008
MMM!

21:16.042 --> 21:19.546
YOU'RE REALLY GONNA LIKE
THE SONG I DOWNLOADED THEN.

21:19.579 --> 21:21.047
[Kenny Loggins'
Highway to the Danger Zone]

21:21.080 --> 21:22.615
OH!

21:22.649 --> 21:24.050
*

21:24.083 --> 21:27.554
UM, I'M GONNA GO DO
PAPERWORK IN THE OTHER ROOM.

21:27.587 --> 21:29.889
HEY, GOOSE,
IT'S MAVERICK.

21:29.922 --> 21:31.824
YOU WANNA HAVE SOME SEX
TONIGHT?

21:31.858 --> 21:33.526
(Mindy)
DON'T CALL ME GOOSE!
